-- Paraguay's Lugo Names Commander to Oversee Anti-Guerrilla Actions in North
-- Bill Faries
-- 2010-04-26T12:26:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-04-26/paraguay-s-lugo-names-commander-to-oversee-anti-guerrilla-actions-in-north.html

          
          
             Paraguay President Fernando Lugo
named Brigadier General Ramon Bartolome Pineda to lead efforts
to subdue the Paraguayan Peopleâ€™s Army, a rebel group the
government blames for assassinations of police and civilians.  
 Pineda will oversee a group of troops and police officers
that has 30 days to pursue the guerrillas under a law passed
April 24 that makes it easier to arrest and detain suspected
rebels in five northern provinces, according to the presidential
website.  
